The libusb driver installation for Win 8 and Win 10 is automated by Zadig, http://zadig.akeo.ie/
The executable is digitally signed and the signature should state: "Akeo Consulting"

1. connect the GPIO board to the computer
2. start the installer
3. the bottom of the window should read "1 device found"
   If it reads "0 devices found" instead, please check the USB connection of the board
4. press the "Install driver" button
5. verify operation by starting the command line and entering:
   controlio -v getport

